  "response_text": "Here's a simple and balanced 7-day meal plan for someone with a gluten allergy. This plan focuses on whole foods that are naturally gluten-free. Always ensure that any packaged products you use are certified gluten-free to avoid cross-contamination.\n\n### Day 1\n**Breakfast:** Smoothie with spinach, banana, almond milk, and chia seeds.  \n**Lunch:** Quinoa salad with cherry tomatoes, cucumber, bell pepper, and a lemon-olive oil dressing.  \n**Snack:** Carrot sticks with hummus.  \n**Dinner:** Grilled chicken breast with roasted sweet potatoes and steamed broccoli.\n\n### Day 2\n**Breakfast:** Greek yogurt with mixed berries and honey.  \n**Lunch:** Lettuce wraps with turkey, avocado, and salsa.  \n**Snack:** Apple slices with almond butter.  \n**Dinner:** Baked salmon with asparagus and quinoa.\n\n### Day 3\n**Breakfast:** Oatmeal made with gluten-free oats topped with sliced banana and walnuts.  \n**Lunch:** Chickpea salad with diced cucumbers, red onion, parsley, and vinaigrette.  \n**Snack:** Rice cakes with peanut butter.  \n**Dinner:** Stir-fried tofu with mixed vegetables (bell peppers, broccoli, carrots) served over brown rice.\n\n### Day 4\n**Breakfast:** Scrambled eggs with spinach and tomatoes.  \n**Lunch:** Black bean soup with a side of avocado slices.  \n**Snack:** Mixed nuts (ensure they are gluten-free).  \n**Dinner:** Grilled shrimp tacos in corn tortillas with cabbage slaw and lime.\n\n### Day 5\n**Breakfast:** Chia pudding made with almond milk, topped with sliced kiwi and coconut flakes.  \n**Lunch:** Caprese salad with fresh mozzarella, tomatoes, basil, and balsamic glaze.  \n**Snack:** Celery sticks with cream cheese.  \n**Dinner:** Stuffed bell peppers with ground turkey, quinoa, and diced tomatoes.\n\n### Day 6\n**Breakfast:** Smoothie bowl with frozen berries, almond milk, topped with sliced almonds and coconut flakes.  \n**Lunch:** Zucchini noodles with pesto and cherry tomatoes.  \n**Snack:** Hard-boiled eggs.  \n**Dinner:** Baked chicken thighs with roasted Brussels sprouts and carrots.\n\n### Day 7\n**Breakfast:** Sweet potato hash with onions and bell peppers topped with a fried egg.  \n**Lunch:** Lentil salad with diced bell peppers, onions, and a vinaigrette.  \n**Snack:** Sliced cucumber with guacamole.  \n**Dinner:** Grilled steak with a side of mashed cauliflower and steamed green beans.\n\n### Tips:\n- Always check labels for gluten-containing ingredients in processed foods.\n- Incorporate a variety of fruits, vegetables, lean proteins, and healthy fats for balanced nutrition.\n- Stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water throughout the day.\n- Consider adding gluten-free grains like brown rice, quinoa, and millet to your meals for variety. \n\nFeel free to adjust portion sizes and snacks according to your individual needs and preferences!",
